<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="78.[778,1373,1261,1689]" pageId="78" pageNumber="136">
Some DNA sequence data indicate a position basal or outside 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brisson" authorityYear="1762" box="[1132,1240,1419,1452]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="136" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pteropus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1825" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="136" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="personatus">Pteropus personatus</taxonomicName>
is the only member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1825" box="[1236,1373,1459,1492]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chiroptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="136" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="personatus">personatus</taxonomicName>
species group. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
